  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003ELaser therapy is clinically proven to be effective for pain management - but how does it work? In this free webinar, you\u0026rsquo;ll learn the basics of how laser therapy and photoceuticals work and how to capitalize on its many clinical applications to enhance patient outcomes in your practice.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EWhether you\u0026rsquo;re new to laser therapy or just need a quick refresher, this webinar will give you a basic working knowledge of this modality. Dr. Carraway and Professor Eells will cover the history of photobiomodulation (PBM), explain mechanisms of action, and share a few clinical uses that might surprise you.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EWebinar attendees will come away with an improved understanding of:\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\u0022\u003E\u25CF\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp; The physiological effects of PBM\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\u0022\u003E\u25CF\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp; The direct and indirect effects of light absorption in tissue\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\u0022\u003E\u25CF\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp; PBM basic applications\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\u0022\u003E\u25CF\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp; How to expand your clinical usage of PBM\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EJoin Christopher Carraway, DC, DIBCN, CLS, NRCEM, and our special guest, Professor Janis T. Eells, PhD, University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee, Department of Biomedical Sciences, for this lively discussion on laser therapy fundamentals.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E"
}]]></Value>
